# Delivery Provider Order Acceptance Rule

## CRITICAL BUSINESS RULE

**All orders accepted by a delivery provider MUST be from the "Awaiting Dispatch" sub-tab of the supplier dashboard.**

## Definition of "Awaiting Dispatch"

An order is in "Awaiting Dispatch" status when:
- **ALL** `material_items` for the order have `dispatch_scanned = FALSE`
- The order has at least one `material_item` with matching `supplier_id`
- The order has a valid `po_number` from `purchase_orders`
- The order is NOT already dispatched, in transit, or delivered

## Implementation Requirements

### 1. Validation Before Acceptance

When a delivery provider accepts a delivery request, the system MUST verify:

```typescript
// Pseudo-code validation
const isAwaitingDispatch = 
  order.material_items.every(item => item.dispatch_scanned === false) &&
  order.material_items.some(item => item.supplier_id === order.supplier_id) &&
  order.po_number !== null &&
  order.po_number !== '';
```

### 2. Files That Must Enforce This Rule

- [DeliveryDashboard.tsx](mdc:src/pages/DeliveryDashboard.tsx) - Main delivery provider dashboard
- [DeliveryRequestCard.tsx](mdc:src/components/delivery/DeliveryRequestCard.tsx) - Individual delivery request cards
- [TrackingNumberService.ts](mdc:src/services/TrackingNumberService.ts) - Service handling order acceptance
- [DeliveryIntegrationService.ts](mdc:src/services/DeliveryIntegrationService.ts) - Delivery integration logic
- [notify-delivery-providers/index.ts](mdc:supabase/functions/notify-delivery-providers/index.ts) - Serverless function creating delivery requests

### 3. Database-Level Validation

When creating or accepting delivery requests, ensure:

```sql
-- Only create delivery_requests for orders where:
-- 1. All material_items have dispatch_scanned = FALSE
-- 2. Order has valid po_number
-- 3. Order has material_items with matching supplier_id

SELECT po.id
FROM purchase_orders po
INNER JOIN material_items mi ON mi.purchase_order_id = po.id
WHERE po.po_number IS NOT NULL
  AND po.po_number != ''
  AND mi.supplier_id = po.supplier_id
  AND NOT EXISTS (
    SELECT 1 FROM material_items mi2 
    WHERE mi2.purchase_order_id = po.id 
      AND mi2.dispatch_scanned = TRUE
  )
GROUP BY po.id
HAVING COUNT(mi.id) > 0;
```

### 4. Error Handling

If a delivery provider attempts to accept an order that is NOT in "Awaiting Dispatch":

- **Reject the acceptance** with clear error message
- **Log the attempt** for audit purposes
- **Show user-friendly message**: "This order is not available for delivery. Only orders awaiting dispatch can be accepted."

### 5. UI Display Rules

- Only show delivery requests for orders in "Awaiting Dispatch" status
- Hide or disable "Accept" button for orders that are:
  - Already dispatched (any `material_item` has `dispatch_scanned = TRUE`)
  - In transit (all items dispatched but not all received)
  - Delivered (all items received)

### 6. Real-time Updates

When a supplier dispatches items (scans QR codes):
- Immediately remove the order from delivery provider's available requests
- Update delivery provider dashboard in real-time
- Notify delivery provider if they had the order in their pending list

